City spokesperson Lindela Mashigo says residents have not changed their behaviour since restrictions were made public late last year. JOHANNESBURG The City of Tshwane has imposed water restrictions to residents following a warning from the City's water supplier to effect water rationing.The city has urged residents not to wash cars using hosepipes, or irrigate their gardens between 6pm and 10pm, amongst other measures.Spokesperson Lindela Mashigo says the city has started with the installation of flow regulators to limit high water usage.Mashigo says residents have not changed their behaviour since restrictions were made public late last year. The limitation applies from the date of the notice, until further notice. The restrictions are still on, are still being enforced, so residents still have to comply. [WATCH] Water restrictions still in place despite recent downpours(Edited by Tamsin Wort)